parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fuel tank leak or failure can cause gasoline to spill, potentially leading to fires, explosions, or damage to property and vehicles. It can also cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Gasoline smell or leak
fuel spill under the vehicle
gasoline running from underneath the vehicle
vehicle stalling or losing power
warning lights or messages on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to slow down or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vehicle goes into limp mode
slowing down or losing power
clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
warning lights or messages on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle when braking can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities, as the vehicle may suddenly move forward into traffic or crash into obstacles.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly when the brake pedal is applied
the vehicle takes off without warning
the vehicle continues to accelerate despite applying the brakes
the vehicle crashes into obstacles or other vehicles.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unintended acceleration of the vehicle can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when the vehicle is in motion or stopped in traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without warning
even when the driver has both feet on the brake pedal
and may continue to move forward despite attempts to stop it.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The catastrophic failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become inoperable, leading to accidents, injuries, or strandings.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience grinding noises
jerking movements
or slipping transmissions
and may eventually fail to move forward or reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and catastrophic failure of Continental tires can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Tread separation
sidewall bulging
cord separation
sudden blowout
and loss of tire pressure
often occurring at high speeds (above 70 mph) and under normal operating conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without warning
often when the brakes are applied
and may continue to accelerate even when the brakes are pressed firmly. The engine may rev excessively
and the tachometer may enter the red zone.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes may not respond or may feel soft or spongy
causing the vehicle to continue moving at the same speed or even accelerate despite applying the brakes. The vehicle may not slow down or stop as expected
even when the brakes are pressed firmly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cruise control malfunction can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The cruise control may become active without being engaged
causing the vehicle to accelerate or maintain speed even when the brakes are applied. Pumping the brake pedal may not disengage the cruise control
making it difficult to slow down or stop the vehicle.
